cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper deals with video analysis and processing, specifically fast-forwarding egocentric videos. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The methodology used involves a learning process based on user preferences, which suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component. The paper also discusses the need for video stabilization, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of video-sharing websites, which suggests an information retrieval (cs.IR) component.
